Certainly! Below is a simple JavaScript program that takes an input string and sorts the characters in alphabetical order:

```javascript
function sortStringAlphabetically(inputString) {
    // Convert the string into an array of characters
    const charArray = inputString.split('');

    // Sort the array alphabetically
    charArray.sort();

    // Join the sorted array back into a string
    const sortedString = charArray.join('');

    return sortedString;
}

// Example usage:
const input = "example";
const sortedOutput = sortStringAlphabetically(input);
console.log(`Sorted string: ${sortedOutput}`);
```

In this program, the `split('')` method is used to convert the input string into an array of characters. The `sort()` method then sorts the array alphabetically. Finally, the `join('')` method is used to convert the sorted array back into a string. You can test this function with different input strings to see how it sorts them alphabetically.
